The words which we have under consideration, spoken by the Sanhedrim to Pilate, seem to refer wholly to the reason we have already mentioned: “ It is not lawful for us to put any man to death.'' Why is it not lawful? Because, being forced by the necessity of the times, we retired from the 100111 Gazfflz, where if we sit not, neither we ourselves nor any court under us can take any cognizance of causes of life and-death.
